Using a wrapping $if (not valid to BDScript 2)
If you get the error: Expected 2 numbers in X>NUM you can use a wrapping $if to bypass it
$if is executed before everything, therefore bypassing $onlyIf, $argsCheck and others, an easy way to bypass this error is to do the same checks those do, but with $if.

Example:
```
$if[$message[1]>2]
it's higher then 2
$else
it's lower then 2
$endif
```
The above code will error if you use a word instead of a number in $message[1], but here is how to bypass that:
```
$if[$isNumber[$message[1]]==true]
$if[$message[1]>2]
it's higher then 2
$else
it's lower then 2
$endif
$endif
```

Now the $if with $isNumber is used before the $if with the numbers, if you didn't provide a number as $message[1] the second $if won't run and therefore won't error.

-Fixes the issue where the EGS version of the game was crashing on startup for some users.
